article.headline: Air Force 83, Colorado State 46
article.story:
FORT COLLINS, Colo. (AP) -- Lindsay Thomas scored a career-high
19 points as Colorado State rode a 21-0 start to an 83-46 rout of
Air Force Saturday night.

Vanessa Espinoza and Melissa Dennett added 18 points each as
Colorado State (12-8, 3-4 Mountain West) beat Air Force for the
17th straight time. The Rams shot 51 percent to win their 13th
consecutive home game against the Falcons, who notched their 11th
straight loss.

\ Castillo had nine points to lead Air Force (3-17, 0-7), who
last won in Fort Collins on Nov. 13, 1979. The Falcons shot 34
percent and didn't have a field goal until a jump shot by Jacki
Novak fell with 8:54 left in the first half.

The Rams extended their 12-point lead at the break to 54-32 with
a 10-0 run five minutes into the second. Baskets by Novak and Gwen
Grove got Air Force as close as 56-36 with 12:22 left, but the
Falcons managed only three points over the next eight minutes.

While the Falcons struggled, Colorado State answered with a 19-3
run. Dennett and Espinoza contributed eight and five points,
respectively.

Air Force missed its first nine shots and committed nine
turnovers to fall behind 21-0. Thomas had six points for Colorado
State before Amoy Jackson's two free throws got Air Force on the
board with 10:42 left.

Thomas, 6-for-7 with 16 points in the first half, rebounded a
basket with 3:55 left to put the Rams ahead 35-16. Air Force closed
the gap to 44-29 at halftime with four 3-pointers, two by Jennifer
Roesch.
